{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy",
          "value": "same-origin-allow-popups"
        },
        {
          "key": "Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy",
          "value": "unsafe-none"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

5. Press **Ctrl+S**
6. Commit & Push → message: `fix COOP headers for Google auth`
7. Wait 2 mins for Vercel to redeploy ⏳

---

## Why this fixes it:
```
Problem:
Vercel sets strict COOP headers
→ blocks Google popup from closing properly
→ Firebase auth fails

Fix:
vercel.json tells Vercel to allow popups
→ Google popup opens AND closes correctly
→ Firebase auth succeeds! ✅
